  "source": "Corollary: \"Trichotomy\"\nof: \"Lemma 3.18\"\ngiven: n, m is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. oneOf:\n  . n = m\n  . n \"in\" m\n  . m \"in\" n\nDocumented:\n. description: \"For any $n, m \\in \\omega$, exactly one of the following holds: $n = m$, $n \\in m$, or $m \\in n$. Comparability gives at least one, and Lemma 3.7 rules out more than one.\"\nId: \"92b0c011-730b-4e42-81f8-dcedb68f93d6\"",
